                        Holmes
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d109</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">109</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-10-05T11:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-10-05T11:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/10–549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Holmes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-05T17:00:00+01:00">October 5, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 5—1:43 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3988. In off-record press interview with American correspondents today,
                        Attlee<note n="80" xml:id="d109fn80">Clement R. Atlee, British Prime
                        Minister.</note> is reported to have said in response to question regarding
                    recognition Chinese Communist Government that (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) British
                    Government would proceed slowly, (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) there were many
                    facets of the problem which needed mature deliberation, including the attitude
                    of <pb facs="0112" n="102" xml:id="pg_102"/> Communists toward China’s
                    international obligations, and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) so far as Nationalist
                    Government is concerned all is not yet lost.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Holmes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
